g/2026/01/mechanistic-insights-into-rna-chaperoning-by-ro60-and-la-autoantigens</link><description>现已上线！结构和功能分析阐明了两个 ATP 独立的 RNA 伴侣 Ro60 和 La 识别和展开错误折叠 RNA 的机制。多种非编码 RNA 与这种伴侣机器相关，在维持 RNA 稳态方面发挥着广泛的作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mechanistic-insights-into-rna-chaperoning-by-ro60-and-la-autoantigens.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2026 11:05:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/mechanistic-insights-into-rna-chaperoning-by-ro60-and-la-autoantigens</guid></item><item><title>神经传输调制的全脑计算捕获完整的任务库</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/neurotransmission-modulated-whole-brain-computation-captures-full-task-repertoire</link><description>德科等人。使用神经传递调制（NEMO）全脑模型来灵活地计算广泛的指令集&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neurotransmission-modulated-whole-brain-computation-captures-full-task-repertoire2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2026 10:50:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/neurotransmission-modulated-whole-brain-computation-captures-full-task-repertoire</guid></item><item><title>细胞存活偏差作为肌肉干细胞衰老的机械驱动因素</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/cellular-survivorship-bias-as-a-mechanistic-driver-of-muscle-stem-cell-aging</link><description>衰老的特点是损伤后组织修复和再生能力下降。在骨骼肌中，这种下降主要是由于肌肉干细胞（MuSC）有效促进肌肉再生的功能受损所致。我们发现了这种与衰老相关的功能障碍的原因：细胞生存偏差优先考虑干细胞的持久性而牺牲功能。随着年龄的增长，MuSC 的肿瘤抑制基因 N-myc 下调基因 1 (NDRG1) 的表达增加，该基因通过抑制哺乳动物雷帕霉素靶蛋白 (mTOR) 通路，增加了它们的长期生存潜力，但代价是它们迅速激活和促进​​肌肉再生的能力。这种随年龄增长而延迟的肌肉再生可能是由于有利于长期干细胞存活而不是立即再生能力的权衡所致。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cellular-survivorship-bias-as-a-mechanistic-driver-of-muscle-stem-cell-aging2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2026 10:35:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/cellular-survivorship-bias-as-a-mechanistic-driver-of-muscle-stem-cell-aging</guid></item><item><title>新研究揭示了与驾驶电动汽车相关的令人惊讶的副作用：“它……有立竿见影的影响”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/new-study-reveals-surprising-side-effects-linked-to-driving-electric-vehicles-it-has-an-immediate-impact</link><description>接下来，该研究的作者将研究更多的 ZEV 是否与哮喘相关的住院和急诊就诊次数减少有关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-study-reveals-surprising-side-effects-linked-to-driving-electric-vehicles-it-has-an-immediate-impact.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 01 Feb 2026 10:20:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/01/new-study-reveals-surprising-side-effects-linked-to-driving-electric-vehicles-it-has-an-immediate-impact</guid></item></channel></rss>